<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aikman Knocked Out of Dallas Opener  </HEADLINE>
By STEPHEN HAWKINS
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas (AP) -- Dallas quarterback Troy Aikman was knocked
out of Sunday's season opener with a concussion, and whether he can
return for next week's game was unclear.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was released from a hospital Sunday night after tests
revealed no serious problem.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was hurt when sacked for the fourth time, by Hugh Douglas
and James Darling, about three minutes into the second quarter. He
was replaced by Randall Cunningham, and the Cowboys went on to lose
41-14.
</P>
<P>
   It's the ninth career concussion for Aikman, who is in his 12th
season. He missed two games midway through last season after
sustaining two concussions in eight days.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Dave Campo said he wasn't sure when a decision
would be made concerning Aikman's future playing time. Dallas plays
at Arizona next Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The injury woes mounted on the last Dallas possession when
Cowboys receiver Joey Galloway was carted off the field with a
sprained left knee. He will undergo an MRI on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys acquired Galloway in an offseason trade with Seattle
to be the big-play receiver and basically serve as the replacement
for Michael Irvin, who was forced to retire because of a neck
injury. He was also listed as the emergency third-string
quarterback behind Aikman and Cunningham in the opener.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was 0-for-5 passing with an interception, finishing
without a completion for only the second time in his 155 career
starts. The other time was Dec. 23, 1990, also against
Philadelphia, when he attempted only one pass before separating his
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Cunningham, signed by the Cowboys as a free agent during the
offseason, played the first 11 of his 15 NFL seasons for
Philadelphia. After missing much of training camp with soreness in
his throwing shoulder, Cunningham completed 13 of 26 passes for 135
yards with one touchdown and one interception -- and was sacked only
once.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm pretty much getting zoned into what we do now, and
starting to get along with the system,'' said Cunningham, who
suffered a sprained right thumb in the game. ''I don't have the
timing and everything, but it will come.''
</P>
<P>
   While the Cowboys carried only two quarterbacks on their opening
roster, undrafted rookie Clint Stoerner is on the practice squad.
Stoerner played most of the final preseason game for Dallas after
beating out Paul Justin as the apparent third stringer.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys gave up two first-round draft picks and a
seven-year, $42 million contract for Galloway to catch passes -- not
throw them. He did have four catches for 62 yards, including a
4-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
