<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cowboys Lose Aikman, Galloway  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   The Dallas Cowboys' season went sour in a hurry.
<TEXT>
<P>
   While en route to a 41-14 defeat at home to Philadelphia,
quarterback Troy Aikman was knocked out of Sunday's season opener
with a concussion.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was released from a hospital Sunday night after tests
revealed no serious problem, but it was unclear if he would play
next Sunday night at Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was hurt while being sacked for the fourth time, by Hugh
Douglas and James Darling, about three minutes into the second
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Randall Cunningham replaced Aikman and completed half of his 26
passes for 135 yards. Aikman was 0-for-5 with an interception.
</P>
<P>
   It's the ninth career concussion for Aikman, who is in his 12th
season. He missed two games midway through last season after
sustaining two concussions in eight days.
</P>
<P>
   The injury woes mounted on Dallas' last possession when receiver
Joey Galloway, who scored the Cowboys' only touchdown, was carted
off the field with a sprained left knee. He will undergo an MRI on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Elsewhere:
</P>
<P>
   San Francisco's Lance Schulters, a Pro Bowl safety last season,
was knocked out of the game on the first play from scrimmage in the
second half of the 49ers' 36-28 loss to Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   A pile of players rolled into Schulters' left ankle. X-rays were
negative, but he will undergo an MRI on Monday to determine if the
injury is more serious than a sprain.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay running back Warrick Dunn left the Buccaneers' 21-16
victory at New England after hurting his right shoulder with five
minutes left in the first half. He returned early in the third
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals left tackle L.J. Shelton sprained his right knee on
the first play from scrimmage against the New York Giants and did
not return. Arizona fullback Joel Makovicka left in the fourth
quarter with a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   Giants safety Sam Garnes, who left the game in the third quarter
with cramps, sustained a concussion with 2:57 to go.
</P>
<P>
   Mike McKenzie, Green Bay's top cornerback, left with a bruised
quadriceps in the second half, and the New York Jets exploited his
absence in the second half for a 20-16 victory over the Packers.
</P>
<P>
   The Pittsburgh Steelers played the final three quarters of their
16-0 loss to Baltimore without run-stuffing linebacker Levon
Kirkland, who sprained an ankle.
</P>
<P>
   San Diego defensive end Al Fontenot was helped off the field at
the half against Oakland with what appeared to be a sprained left
ankle. The Chargers already lost DE Raylee Johnson for the season
with a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City guard Dave Szott went out early in the first quarter
against Indianapolis with a sprained right elbow.
</P>
<P>
   Jacksonville tight end Damon Jones sprained his right knee on
the second play from scrimmage against Cleveland and didn't return.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota's Chris Liwienski made his first start at left guard
in place of Corbin Lacina, but was replaced by Brad Badger after
spraining his right knee. Liwienski is expected to miss up to three
weeks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
