<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mom, 2 children killed in apartment  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   YONKERS, N.Y. (AP) - A 28-year-old woman and two of her young
children were killed in their apartment early Sunday morning, The
Journal News reported.
</P>
<P>
   A third child, a 9-year-old boy, was hospitalized but was
expected to live, said Westchester County District Attorney Jeanine
Pirro, who declined to provide details on what police found at the
first-floor apartment at 55 Maple St.
</P>
<P>
   A 23-year-old man, possibly the woman's boyfriend, also was
hospitalized with apparent stab wounds, law enforcement officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   The victims, Patricia Torres, 28, Ashley Dominguez, 4, and
William Santiago, 7, were found shortly before 8 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   The 9-year-old boy was in critical condition at Jacobi Medical
Center in the Bronx.
</P>
<P>
   ''As you can imagine, a homicide scene with a mother and two
children is very disturbing,'' said Pirro, the district attorney.
''We are doing everything we can to make sure the case we put
together, if it is prosecuted, is a solid one.''
</P>
<P>
   Yonkers police declined to release information.
</P>
<P>
   Iklass Ibrahim, the landlord and owner of 55 and 57 Maple St.,
said that the 23-year-old man is Torres boyfriend and that the two
had a stormy relationship.
</P>
<P>
   ''She was a nice tenant, but she had a lot of problems with
him,'' Ibrahim said.
</P>
<P>
   Ibrahim said that the couple lived together with the children
and that she had received many complaints from tenants who called
to inform her that Torres and her boyfriend were fighting or
playing music loudly.
</P>
<P>
   No other information was immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
