<HEADLINE> Bus Crash in Pakistan Kills 21  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAHORE, Pakistan (AP) -- A speeding bus went out of control near
the eastern border city of Lahore and plunged into a roadside canal
overnight, killing at least 21 people and injuring 30 others,
police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The bus careened off a narrow bridge while overtaking a truck 30
miles south of Lahore, they said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said have found 21 bodies so far, but feared at least 35
were dead.
</P>
<P>
   No other details were immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
