<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes in Russian Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- A bomb exploded Monday in a market in the central
Russian city of Ryazan, killing two people and wounding several
others, an emergency official said.
</P>
<P>
   The blast tore through the market at about 8:30 a.m. in the
small industrial city about 120 miles south of Moscow, said Marina
Ryklina, a spokesman with the Ministry of Emergency Situations.
</P>
<P>
   There was no immediate information on a possible motive, she
said.
</P>
<P>
   The explosion followed an Aug. 12 bomb attack in a crowded
underground passageway in Moscow which killed 12 people and wounded
more than 100.
</P>
<P>
   The blast Monday came on the first anniversary of an apartment
bombing in Buinaksk in southern Russia that killed 64 people.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities blamed Chechen rebels for the Buinaksk bombing and
three other apartment explosions last September that killed a total
of about 300 people and resulted in Russian forces moving into
Chechnya.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
