<HEADLINE> Crown Princess Victoria confirms she has boyfriend in NYC  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) - Crown Princess Victoria is going steady
with a New York City university student, but she's not ready to
talk about marriage.
</P>
<P>
   The 23-year-old princess is dating Daniel Collert, 25, stepson
of prominent Swedish banker Goeran Collert and a student at
Columbia University.
</P>
<P>
   ''Yes, it's correct, it's correct,'' the princess told the daily
tabloid Expressen when asked if Collert were her steady boyfriend.
''But all those rumors about marriage and such things are rather
ridiculous to discuss.''
</P>
<P>
   The court never directly comments on the royal family's personal
affairs, but spokeswoman Elisabeth Tarras-Wahlberg confirmed the
information published Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''The princess has been correctly quoted,'' Tarras-Wahlberg
said.
</P>
<P>
   The princess and the student have known each other for seven
years, according to Expressen.
</P>
<P>
   Victoria, the eldest child of King Carl XVI Gustaf and Queen
Silvia, plans to visit New York next week to attend the Sept. 12
opening of the U.N. General Assembly. She will return to Sweden a
couple of weeks later to continue her royal duties as the heir to
the throne.
</P>
<P>
   Victoria has studied at universities in Angers, France, and in
Connecticut.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
