<HEADLINE> Remaining Key Dates for 2000 Census  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Remaining key dates for the 2000 census:
<TEXT>
<P>
   --Dec. 31: Delivery of actual head count (non-sampled) data to
President Clinton. Data must be used for purposes of reapportioning
of congressional seats.
</P>
<P>
   --Feb. 2001: From Commerce or Census Bureau, decision due on
whether to release sampled census results.
</P>
<P>
   --April 1, 2001: If approved, sampled data is released by this
date. States have option to use sampled population count when
redrawing congressional and state legislative boundaries.
</P>
<P>
   Source: U.S. Census Bureau.
</P>
</TEXT>
