<HEADLINE> Lost Weekend for Christina Aguilera  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -- It was a weekend pop star Christina
Aguilera would sooner forget.
</P>
<P>
   First, she lost her voice, forcing her to cancel a scheduled
appearance at the New York State Fair on Sunday night. Then
souvenir-hunters stole golf clubs, pyrotechnics and a gym bag worth
more than $1,000 from her tour bus.
</P>
<P>
   Two Syracuse University students who had been partying with
Aguilera's crew members on the bus while it was parked outside a
hotel on campus were charged with larceny and burglary, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   None of the items belonged to Aguilera.
</P>
<P>
   Aguilera, whose hits include ''Genie in a Bottle'' and ''I Turn
to You,'' will try to reschedule the fair concert for some time in
the next two weeks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
