<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Princess Victoria Not Ready To Wed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) -- Crown Princess Victoria is going
steady, but she's not ready to talk about marriage.
</P>
<P>
   The 23-year-old princess is dating Daniel Collert, 25, stepson
of prominent Swedish banker Goeran Collert and a student at
Columbia University in New York.
</P>
<P>
   ''Yes, it's correct,'' the princess told the daily tabloid
Expressen when asked if Collert was her steady boyfriend. ''But all
those rumors about marriage and such things are rather ridiculous
to discuss.''
</P>
<P>
   The two have known each other for seven years, according to
Expressen.
</P>
<P>
   Victoria, the eldest child of King Carl XVI Gustaf and Queen
Silvia, plans to visit New York next week to attend the Sept. 12
opening of the United Nations General Assembly. She will return to
Sweden a couple of weeks later to continue her royal duties as the
heir to the throne.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
