<HEADLINE> Police identify drowning victim  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) - Police have identified a woman who drowned
while snorkeling in prohibited waters on Cayuga Lake.
</P>
<P>
   Juri Zalalutdinov, 28, of Ithaca, vanished Saturday while
snorkeling with her husband north of Taughannoch Falls State Park.
Divers recovered her body on Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
   State police said the area is off-limits to swimmers.
</P>
