<HEADLINE> Racetrack parking lot owner Matthew J. Murray dead at 86  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Matthew J. Murray, a former horseman and owner
of the Olympic Parking Service at a number of racetracks, died
Monday. He was 86.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to operating the parking facilities at Aqueduct,
Belmont Park, Saratoga Springs and Delaware Park, Murray became a
horseman and ran Murray Stables from 1960-1975. He also was a
member of the New York Racing Association Turf and Field Club.
</P>
<P>
   Murray also taught labor law at Fordham University from 1960 to
1980. He had a master's in theology from Fordham and a masters in
economics from New York University.
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by a daughter and five sons. His wife of 51
years, Rita, died in 1991.
</P>
