<HEADLINE> Orioles 3, Twins 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Jose Mercedes won for the eighth time in nine
decisions since the All-Star break, leading the Baltimore Orioles
to a 3-2 win over the Minnesota Twins on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Mercedes (11-5), the only Orioles starter with a winning record,
allowed one run and seven hits in 6 2-3 innings. His second-half
record is tied for the best mark in the AL with Pedro Martinez.
</P>
<P>
   Mercedes, coming off a two-hitter against Detroit, walked one
and struck out five. The only run he allowed came on a homer by
David Ortiz.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan Kohlmeier pitched the ninth for Baltimore and earned his
ninth save in as many tries. With the bases loaded and one out,
Kohlmeier struck out Cristian Guzman and got Matt Lawton to fly out
to the fence in right-center to end it.
</P>
<P>
   Rookie Mark Redman (12-8) gave up eight hits and two runs in
seven innings for the Twins, who lost for the fifth time in six
games. Redman, who leads majors in wins by a rookie, lost his
second straight game after winning seven of his previous nine
starts.
