<HEADLINE> Indians Add Three Players  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- Right-hander David Riske, who had surgery May 5
to remove a bulging disc in his lower back, was activated Monday by
the Cleveland Indians.
</P>
<P>
   The Indians also recalled left-hander Tom Martin from Triple-A
Buffalo and shortstop John McDonald from Class-A Kinston.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Riske on the 40-man roster, minor-league
right-hander Jamie Brown was placed on the 60-day disabled list
with a lower back injury.
</P>
<P>
   ''I like what I've seen of Riske and we're going to use him,''
manager Charlie Manuel said. ''He's got some sneak on his fastball
and isn't afraid to go out there against anybody.''
</P>
<P>
   Riske went 1-1 late last season for Cleveland, but was injured
in spring training this year.
</P>
<P>
   Martin has split the 2000 season between Cleveland, where he was
1-0 with a 4.40 ERA in 27 games, and Buffalo, where he was 0-1 with
a 3.60 ERA in nine games.
</P>
<P>
   McDonald appeared in two games with the Indians earlier this
season before being optioned to Kinston last Thursday.
</P>
