<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Activate Castilla  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays activated third
baseman Vinny Castilla from the disabled list Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Devil Rays also recalled right-handed pitchers Dan Wheeler
and Travis Harper from Triple-A Durham.
</P>
<P>
   Harper and Castilla did not play, but Wheeler pitched one
scoreless inning of relief Monday in a 5-1 loss to Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
   Castilla had never been on the disabled list before this season,
but has missed 63 games and been sidelined three separate times.
</P>
