<HEADLINE> Man walks out house, falls off cliff to river  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FILLMORE, N.Y. (AP) - A 39-year-old man apparently walked out
the back door of a friends house early Saturday morning, fell into
the Genesee River and drowned, police said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Police divers pulled the body of Charles E. Young of Fillmore
from about 15 feet of water at about 9 a.m. Sunday morning. He was
pronounced dead at the scene and his body has been sent to the
Monroe County Medical Examiner's Office for examination. The
preliminary cause of death is listed as accidental drowning, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Young was at the home of Victor Prial and apparently went out
the back door at about 2 a.m. on Saturday. Some 36 feet from the
back of the home the ground drops straight down about 15 to 20 feet
to the river, police said.
</P>
<P>
   No charges have been filed and police say the death appears to
be accidental.
</P>
</TEXT>
