<HEADLINE> MetroStars Call Up Paul Grafer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SECAUCUS, N.J. (AP) -- The New York-New Jersey MetroStars called
up goaltender Paul Grafer from the Long Island Rough Riders on
Monday to replace Olympic-bound Tim Howard on the roster.
</P>
<P>
   Grafer, who is 16-9-3 with a 1.29 goals against average with
Long Island in the A-League, is listed as the probable starter for
the MetroStars in Tuesday night's MLS regular-season home finale
against the Miami Fusion.
</P>
<P>
   MetroStars general manager Nick Sakiewicz said the team reached
an agreement with Long Island that will enable Grafer to play with
both teams in their playoff runs. The Rough Riders are a minor
league affiliate of the MetroStars.
</P>
<P>
   Grafer, 26, a native of Port Washington, N.Y., helped the Rough
Riders (16-9-3) clinch their first-ever A-League Northeast Division
crown by beating Toronto 1-0 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Grafer played 13 games for Colorado of the MLS during parts of
the 1997 and 1998 seasons. He had a 1-12 record.
</P>
