<HEADLINE> Powerful Toy Wins Cane Pace  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FREEHOLD, N.J. (AP) -- Powerful Toy held off a late charge by
favored Astreos and survived a foul claim to win the $331,350 Cane
Pace at Freehold Raceway on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Driven by Luc Ouellette, Powerful Toy covered the mile in the
opening leg of pacing's Triple Crown in 1:51.4, beating Astreos and
driver Chris Christoforou by a half-length.
</P>
<P>
   Christoforou said Ouellette and Powerful Toy impeded Astreos in
the stretch, but the judges disallowed the claim.
</P>
<P>
   ''This horse just turned in his best race ever,'' Ouellette
said. ''We found out last week that he's better on the front end.
He likes this track and he likes half-mile tracks in general.
</P>
<P>
   ''He (Astreos) was at my bridle at the three-quarters, but he
wasn't gaining. He got close in the stretch, but I wasn't really
worried that he'd get by.''
</P>
<P>
   Powerful Toy paid $11.80, $5.60, $4.20 in winning for trainer
Monte Gelrod and owners Newman Racing Stable, Dodge A Bullet Stable
and Sampson Street Stable.
</P>
<P>
   Astreos, who matched the track record in winning his elimination
nine days ago, paid $4.20 and $3.20. Art Dot Com paid $5.40 to show
in the eight-horse field.
</P>
</TEXT>
