<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wannstedt's Choices Help Dolphins  </HEADLINE>
By MARK LONG
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAVIE, Fla. (AP) -- The easy choices would have been Damon Huard
and J.J. Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   But Dave Wannstedt, despite stirring up conflict and
controversy, had other plans.
</P>
<P>
   He selected journeymen Jay Fiedler and Lamar Smith to lead his
team into the season, and they helped make Wannstedt a winner in
his first game as team's head coach.
</P>
<P>
   Fiedler completed 15 of 24 passes for 134 yards, and Smith
gained 145 yards on 27 carries in Miami's 23-0 victory over
Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Wannstedt's personnel decisions, considered his downfall in
Chicago, are one of the main reasons the Dolphins are 1-0 and
confidently preparing for Sunday's game at Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   ''They're not all going to fall into place, we know that,''
Wannstedt said Monday. ''You're going to miss. There are going to
be mistakes, but you've just got to make sure you keep those to a
minimum.''
</P>
<P>
   So far, Wannstedt has made all the right moves.
</P>
<P>
   Fiedler, sidelined for much of training camp after having hip
surgery, didn't throw an interception against the Seahawks.
Wannstedt chose Fiedler over Huard, who started five games in place
of Dan Marino last season, after just one preseason game.
</P>
<P>
   Wannstedt picked Smith over incumbent starter J.J. Johnson, who
led the team in rushing with 558 yards last season.
</P>
<P>
   Offseason acquisitions Thurman Thomas, Bert Emanuel, Leslie
Shepherd and rookie Todd Wade also made impacts in their Dolphins
debut.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas had 31 all-purpose yards, Emanuel and Shepherd combined
for four catches for 46 yards and Wade opened up holes all
afternoon for Smith on the right side of the offensive line.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're supposed to win only three or four more games, so this
is good,'' linebacker Zach Thomas said. ''This is good for
Wannstedt. People were already knocking him.''
</P>
<P>
   About the only move that didn't work Sunday was Emanuel's stint
at quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   The Dolphins were penalized for using Emanuel on a third-and-1
play in the second quarter, something they had done consistently in
the exhibition season.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said Emanuel couldn't enter the game at quarterback
because the Dolphins didn't list him as one of the three
quarterbacks on the ''weekly deactivation report.''
</P>
<P>
   Wannstedt said he was still seeking clarification from the
league on the rule.
</P>
<P>
   ''Obviously there was some mixup,'' Emanuel said. ''I'm not
going to say it's wrong, but I've seen other guys on other teams
run similar packages.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite the mixup, Wannstedt's moves seem to be working -- at
least through Week 1.
</P>
<P>
   ''My experience of going through this stuff before is maybe why
I'm at where I am right now mentally,'' Wannstedt said. ''I'm as
excited today as I was my first win in Chicago eight years ago, but
I approach it a little differently. I know what we've got to do
tonight and I know what we've got to do tomorrow.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-04-00 1933 </TRAILER>
