<HEADLINE> Sting Wins Diana Handicap  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Jerry Bailey ended another highly
successful Saratoga meeting Monday, riding Perfect Sting to a
three-quarter length victory in the $500,000 Diana Handicap.
</P>
<P>
   Bailey finished the meeting with 50 victories to break the
record of 48 he set in 1997. Jorge Chavez was second with 37.
</P>
<P>
   Perfect Sting, the nation's leading female turf runner, won for
the 12th time in 17 career starts. The 4-year-old homebred by Red
Ransom from the Valid Appeal mare, Valid Victress, is undefeated in
four starts this year.
</P>
<P>
   Carrying highweight of 123 pounds, Perfect Sting covered 1 1-8
miles in 1:47 on the firm turf course in the Grade II for fillies
and mares 3 and older.
</P>
<P>
   Perfect Sting earned $300,000 for Stronach Stable to boost her
career earnings to $1,342,042. She paid $3.30, $2.30 and $2.10.
License Fee returned $3.30 and $2.40, and Hello Soso paid $3.20.
</P>
</TEXT>
