<HEADLINE> Teen Shoots Self at Police Station  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNION, S.C. (AP) -- An 18-year-old being questioned about
vandalism grabbed his own gun from a police chief's desk, loaded it
and shot himself while handcuffed in the chief's office, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Ray Thomasson was in critical condition Monday night
after shooting himself Sunday afternoon when Union Police Chief
Russell Roark walked away from the desk during a questioning
session, said State Law Enforcement Division spokesman Hugh Munn.
</P>
<P>
   Police had been questioning Thomasson about a brick that been
thrown through the window of a downtown business, Munn said. Roark
was called to the door, and that's when Thomasson grabbed the gun,
which had been seized by officers who brought him in, Munn said.
</P>
<P>
   Thomasson's hands had been handcuffed in front of his body so he
could wipe away a chemical sprayed in his face during a struggle
with police, Munn said.
</P>
