<HEADLINE> Padres Recall Davey, Maurer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Pitchers Tom Davey and Dave Mauer were recalled
Monday by the San Diego Padres from Triple-A Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   Davey, a right-hander, was 1-2 with a 4.10 ERA in 17 appearances
at Las Vegas since being acquired along with John Mabry from
Seattle for Al Martin on July 31.
</P>
<P>
   Maurer, a left-hander who made his major league debut in July
with the Padres, pitched three scoreless innings in two games.
Maurer went 4-1 with a 3.25 ERA in 35 appearances at Las Vegas.
</P>
